<Page x:Class="AsynAwaitExamples.Steps.Step17_Channels"
      xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
      xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
      xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:AsynAwaitExamples.ViewModels"
      Title="Step 17 - Channels">
    <Page.DataContext>
        <vm:Step17ViewModel/>
    </Page.DataContext>
    <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
        <StackPanel Margin="10">
            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HeaderStyle}" 
                       Text="Step 17: Channel&lt;T&gt; - Async Producer/Consumer"/>

            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource ExplanationStyle}" xml:space="preserve">CHANNELS: A modern, async-friendly message queue for producer/consumer patterns.

A producer writes items into the channel. A consumer reads items out.
They run concurrently and the channel handles all the synchronization.

Bounded channels have a max capacity. When full, the producer WAITS
(backpressure). This prevents memory from growing unbounded.
Unbounded channels have no limit and the producer never waits.

ChannelReader.ReadAllAsync() returns IAsyncEnumerable. Use await foreach!
Call writer.Complete() when done producing to signal "no more items."</TextBlock>

            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="?? Unbounded channel (basic producer/consumer)"
                    Command="{Binding UnboundedChannelCommand}"
                    IsEnabled="{Binding IsRunning, Converter={StaticResource InvertBoolConverter}}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="?? Bounded channel (backpressure demo)"
                    Command="{Binding BoundedChannelCommand}"
                    IsEnabled="{Binding IsRunning, Converter={StaticResource InvertBoolConverter}}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="?? Multiple consumers (fan-out)"
                    Command="{Binding MultipleConsumersCommand}"
                    IsEnabled="{Binding IsRunning, Converter={StaticResource InvertBoolConverter}}"/>

            <TextBox Style="{StaticResource OutputStyle}" Height="300"
                     Text="{Binding OutputText, Mode=OneWay}"/>
        </StackPanel>
    </ScrollViewer>
</Page>
